This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a deep learning-based algorithm for biomedical image segmentation. The use of a sequential attention mechanism and a retina-like representation also suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the focus on biomedical images may make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
